f(x)=\frac{x^2}{1-x}
f(x)=\frac{x^2}{1-x}=\frac{x^2+1-1}{1-x}=\frac{(x+1)(x-1)}{1-x}+\frac{1}{1-x}= -x-1+\frac{1}{1-x}
\sum\limits_{n=0}^{\infty}x^n=\frac{1}{1-x}
